AUTHOR: Osten Sacken

QUALIFICATION: Preoccupied by Pales Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830, Pales Koch, 1850 and Pales Gray, 1866. In his discussion of Pales Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830, Bezzi (1906) mentioned that there was an earlier use of Pales by Meigen, 1800, and although he had not seen that work he provisionally accepted Meigen?s name as a senior homonym, which makes the name available from Bezzi (1906) [cf. ICZN Code Article 11.6.1]; although he failed to include any species. Hendel (1908) gave characters for the genus-group name (reproducing Meigen?s characters) and included the first species, Tipula dorsalis Fabricius, 1781, which is thus the type species by subsequent monotypy. Tipula dorsalis Fabricius, 1781 is currently treated in Nephrotoma Meigen, 1803, which makes Pales Bezzi, 1906 a junior synonym of Nephrotoma Meigen, 1803 (Evenhuis & Pape 2017)
